   Frequently Asked Questions
   How do I suggest or recommend adding content?
   Please refer to the TexasOnline link policy then send an email message
   to our webmaster@www.state.tx.us.
   How do I email the governor?
   There are a few easy steps, either visit the Governor's website or open
   an email message.
   Who can answer a general question about Texas history?
   Most information about Texas' history is contained within the Texas
   State Library. You may access the State Library site by selecting the
   link or from the TexasOnline site.
   I have problems accessing/viewing the site.
   There are several options which may detract from the complete
   successful viewing of TexasOnline. This site is compatible with
   browsers of 4.0 or greater. It may be possible that a browser update is
   required for successful viewing. Other options for consideration are:
   checking the Internet connection to the machine, or checking with the
   Internet Service Provider (ISP). If problems persist, please contact
   the TexasOnline webmaster@www.state.tx.us.
   I renewed my Texas Driver License or ID card using TexasOnline but have
   not received my license.
   Thank you for using TexasOnline to renew your license or ID card.
   Generally, it takes a few weeks to process and receive renewed Driver
   Licenses or ID cards. To confirm the status of your request, please
   contact the Department of Public Safety (DPS) at (512) 424-2600 or
   TexasOnline. When contacting DPS or TexasOnline, please have the
   transaction number, amount and date of your renewal available.
   I need to change my address, may I do that using TexasOnline?
   Thank you for using TexasOnline to renew your license or ID card.
   Unfortunately, changing an address is not currently available using
   TexasOnline. To perform your request, please contact the Department of
   Public Safety (DPS) at (512) 424-2600.
   I renewed my Texas Driver License or ID card using TexasOnline and
   would like to receive a receipt.
   Thank you for using TexasOnline to renew your license or ID card. The
   web page from TexasOnline serves as the transaction receipt. Please
   print the receipt page and retain it for your records. Should you have
   further questions, please contact the Department of Public Safety (DPS)
   at (512) 424-2600 or TexasOnline. When contacting DPS or TexasOnline,
   please have the trace number, amount and date of your renewal
   available.

